---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---
<BaseLayout title="About this blog" lang="en" altPath="/about/">
  <article class="article">
    <h1>About this blog</h1>
    <p class="lead">
      A hobby blog that tours Tokyo's major office towers and high-rise residences, one building at a time.
    </p>

    <dl class="about-meta">
      <div><dt>Run by</dt><dd>The Built Japan editorial team</dd></div>
      <div><dt>Updates</dt><dd>One or two new building articles published every morning</dd></div>
      <div><dt>Coverage</dt><dd>Continuously adding Tokyo high-rises (browse the <a href="/en/database/">building database</a>)</dd></div>
      <div><dt>Social</dt><dd><a href="https://x.com/builtjapan" target="_blank" rel="noopener">X @builtjapan</a> for new posts</dd></div>
    </dl>

    <h2>What we cover</h2>
    <p>
      Drawing on publicly available information, we introduce each building's appeal as architecture and its
      impact on the city — completion year, height, number of floors, and the background of the development.
      We feature not only new towers but also established landmarks that have become part of the cityscape.
      It's also meant as a guide for visitors who want to understand the buildings that shape Tokyo's skyline.
    </p>
    <h2>What we don't cover</h2>
    <p>
      We do not handle personal information about residents or tenants, details related to building security,
      or price forecasts and investment advice. For residences, we limit ourselves to the perspective of
      "architecture and streetscape" and take care to respect privacy.
    </p>
    <h2>About accuracy</h2>
    <p>
      Article drafts are generated by AI, while the factual data (completion year, height, etc.) is based on
      public information prepared by the editor. Because errors are still possible, articles marked
      "Unverified" are awaiting the editor's confirmation. If you notice a mistake, please let us know
      via <a href="https://x.com/builtjapan" target="_blank" rel="noopener">X (@builtjapan)</a>.
    </p>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
